{
  "Earthquakes (Seismic Waves, Measurement, Prediction)": "地震(地震波、测量、预测)",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "这个课程涵盖了分析和总结数据集的中心的基本测量方法。 您将学会如何计算和应用平均值、 中位数和模式, 并了解何时最合适 。",
  "What is the epicenter of an earthquake?": "地震的中心是什么?",
  "The epicenter is the point on Earth's surface located directly above the focus (hypocenter) where the earthquake originated underground. Damage and shaking intensity are typically greatest near the epicenter.": "震中是地球表面的点,它直接位于地震起源于地下的焦点(高震中心)上方。 破坏和震动强度通常在震中附近最为严重。",
  "What is liquefaction?": "什么是液化法?",
  "Liquefaction occurs when water-saturated, loosely packed sediment loses its strength during seismic shaking and temporarily behaves like a liquid. This can cause buildings to sink, tilt, or collapse, and is a major hazard in areas built on unconsolidated fill or alluvial deposits.": "当水饱和、散装的沉积物在地震震动期间失去强度,并暂时行为像液体一样时,就会发生液化作用,这可能导致建筑物沉没、倾斜或坍塌,并且是建筑在未加固的填充物或冲积矿床之上的地区的主要危害。",
  "What is a seismograph?": "什么是地震仪?",
  "A seismograph is an instrument that records ground vibrations produced by seismic waves. It works on the principle of inertia, with a suspended mass remaining relatively stationary while the ground and frame move beneath it, producing a seismogram.": "地震仪是一种记录地震波产生的地面振动的仪器,它基于惯性原则运作,悬浮质量保持相对静止,而地面和框架在地下移动,产生地震图。",
  "What is a tsunami?": "什么是海啸?",
  "A tsunami is a series of powerful ocean waves caused by a sudden displacement of a large volume of water, most commonly triggered by an underwater earthquake. Tsunamis can cross entire ocean basins and reach heights of over 30 meters when they strike shore.": "海啸是一连串强大的海洋波浪,其起因是大量水的突然流离,通常由水下地震引发。 海啸可以横跨整个海洋盆地,在撞击海岸时达到30多米的高度。",
  "What is a fault in geology?": "地质学有什么错?",
  "A fault is a fracture or zone of fractures in Earth's crust along which there has been displacement of the sides relative to each other. Faults are classified by their motion: normal (tension), reverse (compression), and strike-slip (shear).": "断层是指地球地壳的断裂或断裂区,其间,两侧相相对相相对地相移。 断层按运动进行分类:正常(加压)、反向(压缩)和罢工滑坡(听觉)。",
  "What is an aftershock?": "什么是余震?",
  "Aftershocks are smaller earthquakes that follow the main shock as the crust adjusts to the stress changes caused by the main rupture. They can continue for weeks, months, or even years and can cause additional damage to already-weakened structures.": "余震是继主要冲击之后的较小地震,因为地壳会适应主要断裂造成的压力变化。 余震可以持续数周、数月甚至数年,并可能对已经变弱的结构造成更多损害。",
  "What is a P-wave?": "什么是P波? (P波)",
  "P-waves (primary waves) are compressional waves where particles move back and forth in the direction of wave travel, like a Slinky being pushed and pulled. They are the fastest seismic waves and can propagate through all states of matter.": "P-波(第一波)是压缩波,粒子在波流中向回移动,就像斯林奇被推拉一样。 它们是最快的地震波,可以在所有物质状态中传播。",
  "What is an S-wave?": "什么是\"S -波\"?",
  "S-waves (secondary or shear waves) cause the ground to move side-to-side, perpendicular to the direction the wave travels. They are slower than P-waves and critically cannot travel through liquids, which revealed that Earth's outer core is liquid.": "S波(二次或剪切波)使地面侧向移动,与波向方向垂直,比P波慢,严重无法通过液体,液体显示地球外核是液体。",
  "What is a seismic hazard map?": "什么是地震危险图?",
  "Seismic hazard maps show the probability and expected intensity of ground shaking for different areas, based on historical seismicity, fault locations, and soil conditions. They are essential tools for building codes, land-use planning, and emergency preparedness.": "地震危害图显示,根据历史地震、断层地点和土壤条件,不同地区的地面震动概率和预期强度,它们是建筑法规、土地使用规划和应急准备的基本工具。",
  "A homeowner in a seismically active region is deciding between building on a lot with solid granite bedrock and a lot with deep, sandy soil near a river. A geologist advises choosing the bedrock site. What is the scientific basis for this recommendation?": "一个地震活跃地区的房主正在决定,在用坚固的花岗岩基岩建很多建筑,在河附近用深沙土建很多建筑。一位地质学家建议选择基岩地。 这项建议的科学依据是什么?",
  "Sandy, water-saturated soil near rivers is highly susceptible to liquefaction and amplifies seismic waves, increasing both shaking intensity and ground failure risk. Solid bedrock is far more stable, transmitting seismic waves without amplifying them and providing firm support for foundations.": "桑迪,河流附近的水饱和土壤极易受到液化作用,并放大地震波,从而增加震动强度和地面故障风险。 坚固的基岩更加稳定,在不放大地震波的情况下传播地震波,并为地基提供坚定的支持。",
  "Outliers and Resistant Measures": "外围和抵抗措施",
  "The Tohoku disaster shows that earthquake preparedness must be comprehensive. While earthquake-resistant buildings saved many lives during the shaking, the tsunami was a secondary hazard that proved far more deadly. Effective preparedness requires addressing multiple hazard types simultaneously.": "东北灾难表明,地震防备必须是全面的。 虽然抗震建筑在震动期间拯救了许多生命,但海啸是次生灾害,其致命性要大得多。 有效的备灾需要同时应对多种灾害类型。",
  "After a major earthquake, a city built on soft, water-saturated sediment experiences far more damage than a nearby city built on solid bedrock, even though both are the same distance from the epicenter. What phenomenon explains this difference?": "在一次大地震之后,一个以软的、饱水的沉积物为基础的城市遭受的破坏远远大于附近一个以坚固的基岩为基础的城市,尽管两者与震中距离相同。 是什么现象解释这种差异?",
  "Soft, unconsolidated sediment amplifies seismic waves, causing stronger and longer shaking compared to solid bedrock. Additionally, saturated sediments may liquefy during shaking, causing the ground to behave like a fluid and buildings to sink or tilt.": "此外,饱和沉淀物在摇晃期间可能会液化,导致地面行为像液体和建筑物沉没或倾斜。",
  "A news report states that a magnitude 5.0 earthquake was felt over a wide area but caused minimal damage, while a magnitude 4.5 earthquake in a different region collapsed several buildings and caused deaths. How is this possible if the first earthquake had a higher magnitude?": "一份新闻报道指出,在大片地区发生了5.0级地震,但造成的破坏最小,而不同区域的4.5级地震摧毁了几座建筑物并造成死亡。 如果第一次地震规模更大,这怎么可能?",
  "Magnitude measures energy released, but damage depends on many factors: depth (shallow earthquakes cause more damage), soil conditions (soft sediment amplifies shaking), building construction quality, and population density. A smaller earthquake in a vulnerable area can be far more destructive.": "巨量测量能释放出来,但损害取决于许多因素:深度(浅地震造成更大的破坏 ) 、 土壤条件(软沉积物放大放大震动 ) 、 建筑质量 、 人口密度。 脆弱地区的小地震破坏力可能更大得多。"
}